programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: In Doncaster, the first to host is glamorous insurance worker Zoe Prince. Shes cooking an Italian-themed menu, despite not being Italian and never having been to Italy. However, that might not be too much of a problem as the other guests dont seem to know their saltimbocca from their vermicelli anyway. With a tip-top menu prepared, Zoe soon learns shes got a lot more on her plate to deal with than just the food.

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: After a fractious first night in Doncaster at Zoes, its now chip shop manager Martyn Bilbys turn to host. Hes pulling out all the stops with his signature dish `Swan Lake: a chocolate eclair swan on a blue jelly lake. Martyn asks his guests to dress formally, but any chance of impressing them goes out the window when Zoe and Signe spot photos of him posing for a `Mr Doncaster body building competition.

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Its day three and host, Trading Standards manager Tracey Hewer, divides opinion more than Marmite. However, this queen of desserts is sure that she can win over her guests with a barrage of cup cakes - for starter, main course and obviously dessert. The guests might all be going home with a dozen carefully packaged cupcakes all of their own, but by the end of the night frozen peas might be of more use.

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Its Latvian lecturer Signe Jases turn to host and shes decided to offer an adventurous menu of Latvian delicacies like herring salad and salted salmon, which might not have been the best idea considering the fussy competitors shes serving. If the guests can get past their first mouthful, Signes sure to put them off the rest of the dinner with some of her more eccentric ideas.

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Its the final night of the competition in Doncaster, and its amusement arcade supplier Barry Hills turn to host. Barry shows off his cooking skills by channelling the spirit of Keith Floyd and mixing, frying and flambeing whilst swigging straight from the bottle, but its not as easy as it looks on the telly.

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: In central England, three culinary heavyweights return to the `Great British Menu kitchen. Two Michelin star chef Daniel Clifford creates a dish called `A Trip to the Chippy, where nothing is as it first appears. That is also the theme for Michelin star chef Richard Bainbridges starter, `banana split, while Will Holland offers up goats cheese mousse, balsamic jelly and gingerbread.

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: Here, the chefs try to impress with their fish courses. Daniel Clifford puts up a creative dish called `Catch of the Day. Does Richard Bainbridges dish titled `Tongue in Cheek live up to its comedy name? Will judge Marcus Wareing find the comedy value in Will Hollands coconut poached brill, crab, celeriac and tomato essence?

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The chefs in central England cook their main courses. Daniel Cliffords main has the same title as Richard Bainbridges fish course, `Tongue in Cheek, but it is a wildly different plate of food; Richard Bainbridge presents guinea fowl in a beef bladder and calls the dish `Which Came First: the Chicken or the Egg; Will Holland offers roast longhorn beef rib eye, bread and bone marrow pudding and parsley paste.

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The chefs in central England have one last chance to impress Marcus Wareing before the final two are chosen to face the judging panel. Will Daniel Cliffords `Going Out with a Bang be good enough? Has Richard Bainbridge dropped the comedy ball with his coffee and chocolate dessert called `Time to Reflect? Or will an unusual dish of parsnip banoffee cake, chocolate tart and parsnip ice cream get Will Holland through?

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: Its decision time for the chefs from the central England region. Only two chefs remain to cook their entire menus for judges Prue Leith, Matthew Fort and Oliver Peyton. The panel is joined by guest judge, comedian and actor Jim Moir, known to millions as Vic Reeves.

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The South West chefs battle it out for a chance to cook at the special banquet. programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The South West chefs cook their fish courses here. programme.title: Attenborough and the Mammoth Graveyard
programme.desc: Sir David Attenborough joins an archaeological dig uncovering Britains biggest mammoth discovery in almost 20 years. Professor Ben Garrod joins the team at DigVentures during the excavation as they try to discover why the mammoths were here and how they died.
